/*
ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W1_EquipmentRental

Class Name: EquipmentRentalApp

Difficulty: Level 2 — Multi-Class Application

Estimated Time: 45–60 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 42 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a campus equipment rental system that stores equipment objects, checks availability,
rents equipment, returns equipment, and counts rented equipment.

Requirements
- Create Equipment objects and store them in an Equipment array.
- Pass the array to a RentalDesk object.
- Print available equipment.
- Rent equipment by code.
- Return equipment by code.
- Count currently rented equipment.

Learning Objective
Practice object arrays, encapsulation, constructors, methods, conditions, loops,
String comparison, and object state updates.
*/